{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1f0fb160-931a-4695-9b11-9584a32ea585","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\n**Tools for analyzing .NET crash dumps:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, easiest):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Then inside the interactive session:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe -lines` — print last exception with source lines\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **`lldb` with SOS** (Linux, more powerful):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   # or\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg / Visual Studio** (Windows) — open the `.dmp` directly.\n\n**Typical first steps to find root cause:**\n```\n> dotnet-dump analyze crash.dmp\n$ pe -lines        # show the exception that caused the crash\n$ clrstack -all    # see all managed stacks\n$ threads          # check for deadlocks or faulting threads\n```\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file? If so, share the path to the `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7d2b7c8d-d828-4e9c-bbd9-0d55b7e92dd9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":465,"requestId":"6807:14859A:AE30A78:BD64339:69FD433D"},"id":"fa40db86-a5d9-48eb-953b-3c544439542a","ti